bug.short_desc: Frequent black screens and Firefox 4 becomes unresponsive

assigned_to.name: Nobody; OK to take it and work on it

long_desc.thetext:
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:2.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0 Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:2.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0
Several times a day since upgrading to Firefox 4, Firefox will become slow and unrseponsivie, and eventually the content area will turn black. The Toolbars and tabs still display but do not function. Firefox will now outright crash on me sometimes as well, just completely close and dissappear. This never occurred before Firefox 4.
Reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. I am not sure how to reproduce this issue other than simply using the browser for an hour or so. It happens several times a day, but I have not seen a pattern in any specific pages or actions that cause it. There are similar reports of black screens in other bug reports, but they mention things like playing videos or viewing content in full screen mode.
This is probably the closest bug, but is marked as resolved, and the user states he can change tabs. I am unable to change tabs once this issue occurs: https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=627437
Actual Results: Black Screen.
Expected Results: No black screen.
My System: Windows 7 64 bit Intel 2 Core 2.4 GHz Abit AB9 Pro Motherboard 8 GB memory NVIDIA GeForce 7950 GT
Extensions: 1Password Firebug Pearl Crescent Page Saver Basic YSlow
I just checked about:crashes, and I only have one crash listed and it was from Firefox 3.6.12 a few months ago.

Does the issue still occur if you start Firefox in Safe Mode? http://support.mozilla.com/en-US/kb/Safe+Mode
How about with a new, empty profile? http://support.mozilla.com/en-US/kb/Basic+Troubleshooting#Make_a_new_profile
If you are getting a crash, but not a crash report a stacktrace would be useful -> https://developer.mozilla.org/en/How_to_get_a_stacktrace_for_a_bug_report

Created attachment 524035 Screenshot of issue
The screen appears gray here rather than black because I clicked on the browser after getting the black screen, and Windows 7 fades everything out when the app is not responding.

(In reply to comment #2) > Does the issue still occur if you start Firefox in Safe Mode? > http://support.mozilla.com/en-US/kb/Safe+Mode > > How about with a new, empty profile? > http://support.mozilla.com/en-US/kb/Basic+Troubleshooting#Make_a_new_profile > > If you are getting a crash, but not a crash report a stacktrace would be useful > -> https://developer.mozilla.org/en/How_to_get_a_stacktrace_for_a_bug_report
I'll have to wait until the weekend to try out Safe Mode and such when I don't need the add-ons for work.

Any update?

Sorry, my weekend ended up being rather hectic. I'll get back with you.(In reply to comment #5) > > I'll have to wait until the weekend to try out Safe Mode and such when I don't > > need the add-ons for work. > > Any update?
Sorry, my weekend ended up being rather hectic. I'll get back with you.

Just another note, something I have noticed is that whenever I get the black screen and then go to the Task Manager to close Firefox, Firefox is always using somewhere between 2.6 - 2.8 GBs of memory. That seems like an awful lot. I have 8 GBs total.

I wouldn't close this ticket quite yet, but it appears the crazy memory leak was resolved by creating a new profile as suggested above. Where with my original profile I was able to get Firefox up to using 1GB of memory with just a few page refreshes of the same page, each refresh increasing the amount of memory, with the new profile, the memory seems to be staying steady at around 220 MBs after each refresh of the same page. I'll let you know if I stop getting the black screens now.
